[{"id":"VR843750","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">What is the approximate bond energy?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR843750_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p>The graph shows the potential energy of two atoms as a function of internuclear distance.</p>\n\n<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"passage\">\n<div class=\"prose style:1\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a graph of a curve in a coordinate plane. The horizontal axis is labeled “Internuclear Distance, in picometers,” and the values 0 through 800, in increments of 200, are indicated. The vertical axis is labeled “Potential Energy, in kilojoules per mole,” and the numbers negative 200 through 200, in increments of 50, are indicated. The curve begins in the top left portion of the graph and moves steeply downward and to the right. It passes through the point with coordinates 150 comma 125 and reaches a potential energy of 0 kilojoules per mole  at 170 picometers . It continues downward and to the right and begins to level off as it reaches a minimum at the point with coordinates 260 comma negative 140. From here, the curve moves upward and to the right at a decreasing rate, passing through the point with coordinates 400 comma negative 80, and the point with coordinates 600 comma negative 25. The curve levels off as it approaches the horizontal axis. The curve moves nearly horizontally to the right until it ends at 800 picometers, just below the horizontal axis.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR843750.g07.svg\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"140 kilojoules per mole\"><math alttext=\"140 kilojoules per mole\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>140</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>kJ/mol</mtext></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-la